      <scopecontent id="aspace_eec1eab8d894f6357f819b3f98e57d4d">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The Lee Hyde papers span the dates 1969 to 1977. They consist of carbons of outgoing correspondence and some incoming correspondence, 1972-1977; copies of his publications and other writings, 1969-1976; and committee reports and memoranda, 1972-1976.</p>
         <p>The papers were given to Yale University Library by Dr. Arthur Viseltear in 1977.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_020ef16247ca1d375b24764d2a54ab72">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Lee Hyde was born in Boston in 1944. He received his B.A. from Harvard in 1965 and M.D. from Case Western ReserveUniversityin 1969. He did an internship in mixed medicine and pediatrics at the University of North Carolina. Following this Hyde spent two years in the Department of Health, Education and Welfare, working in its comprehensive health planning program. From 1972 until 1977 he was a Professional Staff Member with the House Committee on Interstate and Foreign Commerce, specifically with its Subcommittee on Health and the Environment, chaired by Rep. Paul G. Rogers of Florida. Hyde left his Congressional post to complete his residency and pursue his career in medicine.</p>
      </bioghist>
